<doc id="27264" wikidata="Q7696036" url="?curid=27264" title="Telecommunications in São Tomé and Príncipe">
<text>The following is a list of information related to telecommunications in São Tomé and Príncipe.

* TelephonesMain lines in use: 3,000 (1995)
* Telephonesmobile cellular: available, working more accurately than landlines
* Telephone system:
** &quot;domestic:&quot; minimal system
** &quot;international:&quot; satellite earth station – 1 Intelsat (Atlantic Ocean)
* Radio broadcast stations: AM 2, FM 4, shortwave 0 (1998)
* Radios: 38,000 (1997)
* Television broadcast stations: 2 (1997)
* Televisions: 23,000 (1997)
* Internet Service Providers (ISPs): available, dial-up low quality, &quot;broad band&quot; (128/256) very expensive.
* Country code (Top level domain): .st

